title: Wales end 58-year wait for major tournament qualification Wales will... - Barryanddistrictnews.co.uk
text:
Wales will end a 58-year wait to play at a major tournament after qualifying for Euro 2016 next summer. Chris Coleman's side did it the hard way in losing 2-0 to Bosnia-Herzegovina in Zenica, Milan Djuric and Vedad Ibisevic netting second-half goals as Wales slipped to a first defeat of their Group B campaign.
 Barryanddistrictnews.co.uk.
